abstract.text: Perform floating-point arithmetic, transcendental, and trigonometric functions on 128-bit vectors.

inlineContent.text: vfp.h declares a set of floating-point arithmetic, transcendental and trigonometric functions, on 128-bit vectors, using the floating-point types from vecLibTypes.h.
These functions are named with their customary mathematical names, prefixed with the letter “v”, and all except
have the suffix “f” to indicate that they work with single-precision floating-point data. For example,
